{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/cataracts/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"6f26253b-1a92-5f27-8fc7-01f17834ec23","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field fa925b4b-9ed9-4d23-879a-a7f20187ae90 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field fa925b4b-9ed9-4d23-879a-a7f20187ae90 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 29a42623-d7e9-4fa5-87be-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 67b04439-868c-4084-99c3-a7f20187ae90 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 67b04439-868c-4084-99c3-a7f20187ae90 --><!-- begin field d1d34640-c2e4-4846-a8e8-a7f20187ae90 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field d1d34640-c2e4-4846-a8e8-a7f20187ae90 --><!-- begin field a9d6af83-44a1-4935-a21a-a7f20187ae90 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field a9d6af83-44a1-4935-a21a-a7f20187ae90 --><!-- begin field 127f0ab7-e217-484c-9681-a7f20187ae90 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 127f0ab7-e217-484c-9681-a7f20187ae90 --><!-- begin field 6d58f26c-db8e-4801-a75f-a7f20187ae90 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 6d58f26c-db8e-4801-a75f-a7f20187ae90 --><!-- begin field 276a679b-6560-4154-8bb9-a7f20187ae90 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 276a679b-6560-4154-8bb9-a7f20187ae90 --><!-- end item 29a42623-d7e9-4fa5-87be-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"eeb34712-def5-5b38-9125-fec8925c1bcc","topicId":"9a3fe0f5-1b06-4ff6-9a79-2ed4a8f4b2c5","topicName":"Cataracts","slug":"cataracts","lastRevised":"Last revised in MarchÂ 2020","chapters":[{"id":"90f4d5e6-8dee-54a2-b535-a3280c9ff7e9","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"da1f4019-d02d-523b-80ce-e4ba8579b43d","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"87a3b79a-dbff-50b1-a10c-fc54f60080f3","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"cd79c0cf-e5a8-5fb6-99af-3d9e0eaf4b28","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"d0c360ad-3631-54ab-809e-570769cd5aa1","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"8af6938b-ae1b-5c2a-8b8c-826edbed8669","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"9ed0ddb2-07a6-5c9e-86b8-740894cd88e7","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"d3db836f-68b9-5c32-bb04-1d6c9b755015","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"78ff1c73-3038-544d-829b-9c4fa6e07ea0","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"65